                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>6 West 9th street<lb/>
                11th March&#44; 92<lb/></p>
            <p>Reverend Dr. S. Morais.<lb/>
                Highly esteemed Reverend &#38; Friend&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>I take pleasure on behalf of<lb/> my&#44; so dear&#44; Reverend Patient &#38; our daughter&#44;<lb/> to thank you &#40;in their names&#41; for<lb/> your solicitude &#38; sympathy in the<lb/> present suffering which has<lb/> overtaken him.<lb/></p>
            <p>Thank God&#44; that with the worst<lb/> passed&#44; we can today look up<lb/> with joy &#38; thanksgiving to our<lb/> Heavenly Father for permitting us<lb/> to hail this Sabbath Eve&#44; with<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the gladness this Feast&#44; or Purim&#44;<lb/> inspires &#40;to us Israelites.&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>I leave all detail of the hor&#45;<lb/>&#45;rifying occurrence behind&#44; or for the<lb/> happy moment when he shall see you&#44;<lb/> and were it not for the stern reality<lb/> that he is&#44; forcibly&#44; bedridden&#44; presently<lb/> we would remember&#44; only praise<lb/> and gratitude for the new life<lb/> much safer&#44; through merciful<lb/> Providence&#44; to us&#44; &#38; his dear good self&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>May God grant you&#44; with him&#44;<lb/> &#34;length of days&#34; to minister in<lb/> the Divine Service you have so<lb/> spiritually chosen.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>And with my special share<lb/> of highest regard for you&#44;<lb/> worthy dignitary&#44; and reiterated<lb/> assurance &#38; appreciation from<lb/> this home circle&#44; inclusive<lb/> dear Revd. &#38; Mrs A. P. Mendes&#59;<lb/> I am&#44; very sincerely<lb/> Rachel I. Piza.<lb/></p>
            <p>Sabbath eve<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
